Title and purpose  (FIX THE EDA SCRIPT)
State the dataset, the question, and what the EDA is trying to uncover.

Data loading
Show the code that imports libraries and reads the raw data.

Initial data overview
Include dataset shape, column names, variable types, and a few sample rows.


Data cleaning
Show code for missing values, duplicates, type fixes, recoding, or filtering, then explain what changed and why.

Univariate analysis
Look at one variable at a time using summaries and plots such as histograms, boxplots, or bar charts.

Bivariate / correlation analysis
Check relationships between variables using scatterplots, correlation matrices, cross-tabs, or group comparisons.

Key findings
Write short takeaways from the patterns you found, including anything unusual, important, or worth modelling later.

Conclusion and next steps
Summarize what the data suggests and what you would do next for modelling or deeper analysis.